      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Clean the CLASS column by removing leading/trailing spaces and standardizing case\n",
        "data['CLASS'] = data['CLASS'].str.strip().str.upper()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Re-plot the graphs after cleaning\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 6))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Boxplot for AGE vs CLASS\n",
        "sns.boxplot(x='CLASS', y='AGE', data=data, ax=axes[0] , patch_artist=True)\n",
        "axes[0].set_title('Boxplot of AGE vs CLASS')\n",
        "axes[0].set_xlabel('Diabetes Class')\n",
        "axes[0].set_ylabel('Age')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Violin plot for AGE vs CLASS\n",
        "sns.violinplot(x='CLASS', y='AGE', data=data, ax=axes[1], inner='quartile')\n",
        "axes[1].set_title('Violin Plot of AGE vs CLASS')\n",
        "axes[1].set_xlabel('Diabetes Class')\n",
        "axes[1].set_ylabel('Age')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "# Scatter plot for Cholesterol with respect to HDL and LDL\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Use seaborn's scatterplot to visualize the relationship\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(x='HDL', y='LDL', hue='Chol', size='Chol', sizes=(20, 200), data=data, palette='coolwarm', alpha=0.8)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding labels and title\n",
        "plt.title('Scatter Plot of Cholesterol with respect to HDL and LDL')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('HDL (High-Density Lipoprotein)')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('LDL (Low-Density Lipoprotein)')\n",
        "plt.xlim(0, 4)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Show the plot\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]

        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",

        "# Set the plot style\n",
        "sns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",

        "# Create a boxplot to show the distribution of Age across different classes\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Boxplot of AGE vs CLASS\n",
        "sns.boxplot(x='CLASS', y='AGE', data=data)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding labels and title\n",
        "plt.title('Boxplot of Age vs Diabetes Class')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Diabetes Class (Y = Diabetes, P = Prediabetic, N = No Diabetes)')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Age')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Show the plot\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"

        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set the plot style\n",
        "sns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create a count plot to show the distribution of Gender across different Classes\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Count plot for GENDER vs CLASS\n",
        "sns.countplot(x='CLASS', hue='Gender', data=data)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding labels and title\n",
        "plt.title('Count Plot of Gender vs Diabetes Class')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Diabetes Class (Y = Diabetes, P = Prediabetic, N = No Diabetes)')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Count of Individuals')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Show the plot\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"

        "import plotly.express as px\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define color mapping for gender, with dark blue and dark red\n",
        "colors = {'Male': 'darkblue', 'Female': 'darkred', 'M': 'darkblue', 'F': 'darkred'}\n",
        "data['Color'] = data['Gender'].map(colors)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Clean data by removing rows with NaN values in essential columns\n",
        "data_clean = data.dropna(subset=['BMI', 'Chol', 'HbA1c', 'Color'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot if data_clean has rows\n",
        "if not data_clean.empty:\n",
        "    fig = px.scatter_3d(\n",
        "        data_clean,\n",
        "        x='BMI',\n",
        "        y='Chol',\n",
        "        z='HbA1c',\n",
        "        color='Color',\n",
        "        color_discrete_map=colors,\n",
        "        title='3D Scatter Plot of BMI, Cholesterol, and HbA1c by Gender'\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Reduce point size and update axis titles\n",
        "    fig.update_traces(marker=dict(size=3))  # Set marker size to a smaller value\n",
        "    fig.update_layout(scene=dict(\n",
        "        xaxis_title='BMI',\n",
        "        yaxis_title='Cholesterol',\n",
        "        zaxis_title='HbA1c'\n",
        "    ))\n",
        "    fig.show()\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"No data available for plotting after cleaning.\")"
      ]

        "from math import pi\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define categories and relevant columns for radar chart\n",
        "categories = [ 'HbA1c', 'Chol', 'HDL', 'LDL']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ensure AGE column is numeric and filter for the relevant age group\n",
        "data['AGE'] = pd.to_numeric(data['AGE'], errors='coerce')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Filter data for the specified age range (30-50)\n",
        "age_group_data = data[(data['AGE'] >= 30) & (data['AGE'] <= 50)]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate the global min and max for each category to keep scales consistent\n",
        "category_mins = age_group_data[categories].min()\n",
        "category_maxs = age_group_data[categories].max()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize a horizontal plot with three subplots for each class\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6), subplot_kw=dict(polar=True))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Loop through each unique class and its corresponding subplot axis\n",
        "for i, class_label in enumerate(['P', 'Y', 'N']):\n",
        "    class_data = age_group_data[age_group_data['CLASS'] == class_label]\n",
        "\n",
        "    if not class_data.empty:\n",
        "        # Calculate mean values for each category for this class\n",
        "        values = class_data[categories].mean().values.flatten().tolist()\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Normalize values to percentage of max-min range for consistency across plots\n",
        "        normalized_values = [\n",
        "            100 * (val - category_mins[cat]) / (category_maxs[cat] - category_mins[cat])\n",
        "            if category_maxs[cat] != category_mins[cat] else 0\n",
        "            for val, cat in zip(values, categories)\n",
        "        ]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Complete the radar chart loop by appending the first value to the end\n",
        "        normalized_values += normalized_values[:1]\n",
        "        angles = [n / float(len(categories)) * 2 * pi for n in range(len(categories))]\n",
        "        angles += angles[:1]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Plot for each class with a filled area\n",
        "        ax = axes[i]\n",
        "        ax.plot(angles, normalized_values, linewidth=2, linestyle='solid', label=f'Class {class_label}')\n",
        "        ax.fill(angles, normalized_values, alpha=0.3)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Set category labels and title for each subplot\n",
        "        ax.set_xticks(angles[:-1])\n",
        "        ax.set_xticklabels(categories)\n",
        "        #ax.set_yticklabels([])  # Hide radial percentage labels for clarity\n",
        "        ax.set_title(f'Class {class_label}', size=15, color='navy')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add an overall title and show the plot\n",
        "plt.suptitle('Average Health Profile for Age Group 30-50 by Class', size=18, color='darkblue')\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
